        <p><u>Areas of interest</u>: Human-computer interaction · Programming · Reading.</p>

<p>Welcome to my home page! I am Andrew Head, an assistant professor at
the University of Pennsylvania. My group specializes in developing
technology for <span style="font-weight: 500">interactive reading and reasoning</span>. My current goals are to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Help scientists get more out of their readings in less time</li>
  <li>Make math notation everywhere inviting and understandable</li>
  <li>Help programmers comprehend code using AI</li>
  <li>Accelerate programmers in writing, maintaining, and understanding proofs of
correctness about their programs</li>
</ul>

<p>Our projects follow a systems-centric HCI approach. We do in-depth
user studies to understand what people need from their tools. Then, we build
working interactive systems, imbuing them with powerful new interaction design ideas.
We publish our work at ACM CHI and UIST, and other venues focused on information
presentation and programming support.</p>

